// Title: FakeAgent Signed-Application DLL Sideloading
// Status: Hunting query - Untested implementation sketch
// Confidence: High
// Platform: Microsoft Defender XDR
// Telemetry: DeviceImageLoadEvents
// Purpose: Hunt for the process-module pairs observed by Huntress in the
// FakeAgent campaign: renamed JetBrains components loading libcef.dll and an
// IBM SPSS sslconf.exe binary loading tempdir.dll.
// ATT&CK: T1574.002, T1036
//
// Evidence boundary:
// - Each process-module pair is directly supported by the primary source.
// - A match does not prove that the loaded DLL is modified or malicious.
// - File provenance, original filename, signature, prevalence, persistence and
//   follow-on endpoint activity must be reviewed before escalation.
//
// Validation:
// Run over 30-90 days and group distinct process paths, module paths, hashes,
// devices and software owners. Keep as hunting unless benign activity can be
// separated through stable, narrowly scoped attributes.

DeviceImageLoadEvents
| where
    (
        InitiatingProcessFileName in~ ("ClaudeDesktop.exe", "DockerDesktop.exe")
        and FileName =~ "libcef.dll"
    )
    or
    (
        InitiatingProcessFileName =~ "sslconf.exe"
        and FileName =~ "tempdir.dll"
    )
| project
    Timestamp,
    DeviceId,
    DeviceName,
    InitiatingProcessFileName,
    InitiatingProcessFolderPath,
    InitiatingProcessCommandLine,
    FileName,
    FolderPath,
    SHA1,
    InitiatingProcessSHA1,
    ReportId
